(2) The Commission may— (a) require any person dealing with food supplements or any agent, employee, servant or authorised representative of that person to furnish the Commission with information, records and samples that are necessary to enable the Commission monitor food and nutrition matters under this Act; and (b) direct any organisation implementing a food and nutrition programme to implement the programme in a manner that ensures compliance with this Act.
