(5) A person shall not be nominated or appointed as a member of the Board if that person— (a) is not a citizen; (b) has not served at senior management level for at least five years; (c) is an undischarged bankrupt; (d) is legally disqualified from holding the office of a member; (e) has been convicted of an offence under any other written law and sentenced to imprisonment for a period exceeding six months without the option of a fine within a period of five years preceding the date of nomination or appointment; (f) has been found guilty of professional misconduct; or (g) is an employee of the Commission .
