The functions of the Board are to—
approve the policy and strategic plan of the Commission ;
approve the annual budget estimates and audited financial statements of the Commission ;
monitor and evaluate the performance of the Commission against budgets and plans; and
establish and approve guidelines and standards for the purposes of this Act.

(1) A member of the Board shall hold office for a period of three years and may be reappointed for one further period of three years.
